{{ 'about-game.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}


<div class="about-game">
  <div class="about-game__title">
    <h2>ABOUT THE GAME</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="about-game__block">
    <div class="left-side">
      <div class="title">
        <h3>STRATEGY GAME :</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="about">
        <p>As one of six adventurers, each with their own unique talents, you will fight your way through a vast, unrecognizable land filled with dangers and riches. Your goal is to journey through the landscape of Ancient Sumer and find the 4 Ziggurats and collect all of the Map Cards (either through purchase, negotiation, or theft) that will lead you to the great City of Ur where you hope to defeat Nanna the God of Ur.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="right-side">
      <div class="pic">
        <img class="icon icon-cart-empty" src="{{ 'pic.png' | asset_url }}" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-game__block">
    <div class="left-side">

      <div class="pic">
        <img class="icon icon-cart-empty" src="{{ 'pic.png' | asset_url }}" />
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="right-side">
      <div class="title">
        <h3>FUN & COMPETITIVE GAME WITH COUNTLESS REPLAY OPPORTUNITIES :</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="about">
        <p>Experience the excitement of endless possibilities with our game's remarkable tile placement system. The complete randomness of the tiles ensures limitless replayability, guaranteeing that no two games will ever be the same. Prepare for a truly unique and unpredictable adventure each time you play! With the vast assortment of tiles included in the box, you'll find yourself constantly discovering new paths, challenges, and opportunities. The ever-changing landscape of Ancient Sumer invites you to explore different strategies, adapt to unexpected circumstances, and embrace the thrill of uncertainty. To further enhance your gaming experience, we have included a variety of variants right in</p>
      </div>
      <div class="read-more">
        <p>Read more</p>
        <div class="circle"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


